_meanings:
{@--1@} An 
adversative particle meaning ‘but’, ‘on
the contrary’, ‘on the other hand’,
‘nevertheless’; {#sa sarvezAM suKAnAmaMtaM#}
{#yayO . ekaM tu sutamuKadarSanasuKaM na leBe#}  
<ls>K. 59</ls>; {#viparyaye tu piturasyAH#} 
{#samIpanayanamavasTitameva#} <ls>Ś. 5</ls>; (in this sense {#tu#} is
often added to {#kiM#} and {#paraM#}, and {#kiMtu#}
and {#paraMtu#} are, unlike {#tu#}, always used
at the beginning of a sentence).

{@--2@}
And now, on one's part, and;  

{#ekadA tu pratIhArI samupasftyAbravIt#} <ls>K. 8</ls>;
{#rAjA tu tAmAryAM SrutvA'bravIt#} <ls n="K.">12.</ls>

{@--3@}
As to, as regards, as for; {#pravartyatAM#}
{#brAhmaRAnuddiSya pAkaH . caMdroparAgaM prati tu#}
{#kenApi vipralabDAsi#} <ls>Mu. 1</ls>;  
<ls>Māl. 8. 4.</ls>

{@--4@} It sometimes marks a 
difference ({#Beda#}) or superior quality;
{#mfzwaM payo mfzwataraM tu dugDaM#} <ls>G. M.</ls>

{@--5@}
Sometimes it is used as an 
emphatic particle; {#BImastu pAMqavAnAM rOdraH#}
<ls>G. M.</ls>

{@--6@} And sometimes it is
used as a mere expletive; {#nirarTakaM#}
{#tu hItyAdi pUraREkaprayojanaM#} <ls>Chandr. 2. 6.</ls>
